==English==

===Etymology===
{{m|en|May}} could refer to the month or the blossom that accompanies it.
The Term Ne'er cast a clout originally started during the industrial revolution, Clout is a type of hand made nail. during the winter months outside clothing was hung on a nail, during the summer no coats were needed therefore the nail was removed. May was considered the last month of frosts, so it was considered wise to not remove the nail until June.

===Proverb===
{{en-proverb}}

# {{lb|en|regional}} Do not [[change]] from winter [[clothes]] to summer clothes until June, as there is often a sudden [[cold snap]] in May.

